**UPDATE - ISSUE SOLVED**: The issue described above was in fact a routing error in my dispatch.yaml and not a CORS error. I was inputting `&quot;backend-dot-example.appspot.com/*&quot;` in the dispatch.yaml but this file only takes URLs that do NOT include the &quot;-dot-&quot; path. Even though this is the URL you see in your app&#39;s Versions section on the Google App Engine platform, you cannot put the URL with the &quot;-dot-&quot; path in the dispatch file but instead you need to put the URL with the &quot;.&quot; (i.e., &quot;backend.example.appspot.com/*&quot;). However, using this version of the URL did give me a SSL Certificate error (ERR_CERT_COMMON_NAME_INVALID) because apparently only the URL with the &quot;-dot-&quot; path falls under the domain&#39;s SSL Certificates and the one with the &quot;.&quot; path does not.

I ended up finding a simpler, better solution that did not give me any errors. I simply put `&quot;*/api/*&quot;` in the URL on the dispatch.yaml and the POST method is routing correctly to the backend service now without any issues.

Updated dispatch.yaml:
```
# Rules for dispatch file...
# Put specific cases at the top.
dispatch:
# Route the urls that point to the Express backend/&#39;s API calls
  - url: &quot;*/api/*&quot;
    service: backend
# Route all other urls to the React.js frontend
  - url: &quot;*/*&quot;
    service: default
```

